org.gephi.data.attributes.api

Interface AttributeEventData


  • public interface AttributeEventData
    Data associated with an attribute event.
    Author:
    Mathieu Bastian
    See Also:
    AttributeEvent

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      AttributeColumn[] getAddedColumns()
      Returns columns that have been added.
      AttributeColumn[] getRemovedColumns()
      Returns columns that have been removed.
      Object[] getTouchedObjects()
      Returns objects where attribute values have been modified.
      AttributeValue[] getTouchedValues()
      Returns values with the SET_VALUE event.

    • Method Detail

      • getAddedColumns

        AttributeColumn[] getAddedColumns()
        Returns columns that have been added. Look at AttributeEvent.getSource() to know to which AttributeTable.
        Returns:
        the added columns

      • getRemovedColumns

        AttributeColumn[] getRemovedColumns()
        Returns columns that have been removed. Look at AttributeEvent.getSource() to know from which AttributeTable.
        Returns:
        the removed columns

      • getTouchedObjects

        Object[] getTouchedObjects()
        Returns objects where attribute values have been modified. Objects are either NodeData or EdgeData. The index of the returned array is matching with values from getTouchedValues().
        Returns:
        the objects modified with the SET_VALUE event

      • getTouchedValues

        AttributeValue[] getTouchedValues()
        Returns values with the SET_VALUE event. The AttributeValue object contains the new value that has been set. The index of the array is matching with values from getTouchedObjects().
        Returns:
        the new values set with the SET_VALUE event.
